                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <div class="about-contain-div padding-right-div">
                        <p class="common-para mt-0 text-justify">
                            Sulzer looms are a type of shuttleless weaving machine commonly used in the textile industry. They are named after the Swiss company Sulzer, which developed and manufactured these looms.
                        </p>
                        <p class="common-para text-justify">
                            Sulzer looms are known for their high-speed operation and versatility in producing a wide range of fabrics. They utilize a projectile system to insert the weft yarn across the warp threads, eliminating the need for a traditional shuttle. This design allows for faster weaving speeds and reduces the risk of yarn breakage.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>

            <div class="row mt-4">
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <div class="about-contain-div padding-right-div">
                        <h4>Here are some key features and advantages of Sulzer looms:</h4>
                        <p class="common-para mt-0 text-justify">
                            <strong>High Speed:</strong>  Sulzer looms are renowned for their high production rates. They can achieve weaving speeds of several hundred picks per minute, resulting in increased productivity and efficiency.
                        </p>
                        <p class="common-para text-justify">
                            <strong>Versatility:</strong> These looms are suitable for weaving various types of fabrics, including plain weaves, twills, satins, and complex patterns. They can handle a wide range of yarns, including cotton, polyester, silk, and blends.
                        </p>
                        <p class="common-para text-justify">
                            <strong>Precision and Quality:</strong> Sulzer looms offer excellent fabric quality and precise control over the weaving process. They can produce fabrics with consistent selvedges, uniform density, and minimal defects.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-5">
                    <div class="p-4 about-right-div border-remove wow zoomIn animated animated" data-wow-delay=".6s" data-wow-duration="2s" style="visibility: visible; animation-duration: 2s; animation-delay: 0.6s; animation-name: zoomIn;">
                        <img src="~/Content/assets/Images/About/sulzerloom-double.jpeg" class="img-fluid">
                        <strong class="text-center mx-auto d-block">( sulzer loom double )</strong>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row mt-4">
                <div class="col-md-5">
                    <div class="p-4 about-right-div border-remove wow zoomIn animated animated" data-wow-delay=".6s" data-wow-duration="2s" style="visibility: visible; animation-duration: 2s; animation-delay: 0.6s; animation-name: zoomIn;">
                        <img src="~/Content/assets/Images/About/sulzerloom-single.jpeg" class="img-fluid">
                        <strong class="text-center mx-auto d-block">( sulzer loom single )</strong>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <div class="about-contain-div padding-right-div">
                        <p class="common-para mt-0 text-justify">
                            <strong>Reduced Yarn Waste:</strong> The shuttleless design of Sulzer looms eliminates the need for pirn winding and reduces yarn waste compared to conventional shuttle looms. This contributes to cost savings and sustainability in textile production.
                        </p>
                        <p class="common-para text-justify">
                            <strong>Automation and Control:</strong> Modern Sulzer looms feature advanced automation and control systems. They can be equipped with computerized monitoring and adjustments for efficient operation, fault detection, and easy pattern changes.
                        </p>
                        <p class="common-para text-justify">
                            <strong>Wide Loom Width:</strong> Sulzer looms are available in various widths to accommodate different fabric requirements. They can handle large-scale production of wider fabrics, such as upholstery materials and industrial textiles.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>


            </div>

